track_notes: Park next to phone box at NO 5403 7892. Small parking space, 4 vehicles at most. Follow lane (N) to NO 5374 7941. Bear right onto a track to a cottage (noisy but secure dogs).  Turn right (E) in front of the cottage and head for the tree line 250m away, then turn north.  Either cross the ford at NO 5411 7983 or use the two footbridges below. Keep right and continue through gateway at NO 5425 8010. Bear left on track at NO 5441 8044. At NO 5413 8148 keep right to bear around the hill side. At NO 5431 8271 another new track turns right (east), ignore this and continue north and then west more steeply uphill.  There is a nice line of stone grouse butts for a stop out of the wind. After going through a gateway the track  diverges from where it is shown on the map. Continue to NO 5382 8391 where you meet another track, hairpin right up hill. Around NO 5413 8416 go straight on following a less distinct path across a shallow col to the summit and trig point. Quick walking on good surface.
track_title: From Milden Lodge in Glen Esk

track_notes: A longer route from the east following the ridge from Clachnaben. Path is mostly dirt road and easily followable. However easy to miss the grass path leading to the summit. Southerly return to avoid summit conditions of the ridge and also passes Charr Bothy for shelter.
track_title: Mount Battock via Clachnaben from Glen Dye Carpark

track_notes:
This route avoids Clachnaben and easier to cycle. You can also push the bike up the last part for a quicker ride back.

Turn off B974 through an open metal gate and park at the bottom by the Water of Dye.

Cycle path path follows the water around, after 7km turn right up the hill. As it gets steeper you might need to push the bike. You can keep going with the bike for ~11.4km when you turn off the main tracks onto the final ascent to the summit.
